{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}
{{Use South African English|date=November 2012}}
'''Hilton Saven''' is a South Africa businessman, the chairman of [[Mazars]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/200912150483.html|title=South Africa: JSE-Listed Clients Lift Revenue at Mazars|last=Temkin|first=Sanchia|date=15 December 2009|work=allAfrica.com}}</ref> serves on the governing council of Praxity, a global alliance of independent accounting and auditing firms, and was appointed to the Mazars board as co-CEO in December 2009.

==Career==

Saven has been with the firm since January 1975 where he started his articles at the then Musikanth Cohen and Fine. He completed his articles with the firm and moved through the ranks to audit manager, and was then appointed as a Partner in January 1981.  Saven worked in audit for four years until 1985, at which time he moved across to the consultancy division.

In 1986, Saven was appointed to the executive of the South African practice and became managing partner in 1988.  Over the next few years, he was integral in representing Moores Rowland at international level whilst serving on the international Board of Moores Rowland International.  In 1994, he assumed the role of Senior Partner of the South African practice.

In September 2007, Moores Rowland integrated with [[Mazars]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vrl-financial-news.com/accounting/intl-accounting-bulletin/issues/iab-2007/iab416/moores-rowland-south-africa-fi.aspx|title=Moores Rowland South Africa firm joins Mazars Group|last=Hickman|first=Arvind|date=1 May 2008|work=vrl-financial-news.com}}</ref> and became Mazars South Africa,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.beenews.co.za/archives/mazars_moores_rowland_reports_revenue_of_r267_million_and_27_growth.php|title=Mazars Moores Rowland reports revenue of R267 million and 27% growth|date=17 December 2009|work=beenews.co.za}}</ref> of which Saven is Chairman.

==Other activities==

Outside of Mazars, in 2003 Saven was appointed to the board of [[Truworths]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://raisingentrepreneurs.org/blog/2008/10/08/high-expectation-entrepreneurs-education-is-the-key/|title=High-Expectation Entrepreneurs – Education Is The Key|date=8 October 2008|work=raisingentrepreneurs.org}}</ref> a large retail company listed on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange, and is currently serving as their non-executive chairman. He has served as a member on a number of external committees for the [[South African Institute of Chartered Accountants]].

